  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nSplit up version of https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/7418\r\n\r\nStart async process to fetch curated communities as soon as the user logs in. Then once this data is fetched for the first time it should be cached, probably in a table, so that the next time the user logs in, if they navigate to the community directory, and the latest data has not been fetched, then the cached data should be displayed instead.\r\n\r\nOne way to do it is to maybe have a field in the communities table about whether the community is curated and/or featured.\r\nThen just have a query that retrieves only those.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- Curated communities are cached some way or  another\r\n- Opening the app and going to the curated communities portal shows the previous results even before the contract answers\r\n\r\n",
